        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 9:56PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 956 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Sandy Shore Rec Area to
near Bemis to Lake Cochrane Rec Area. Movement was southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Watertown, Clear Lake, Castlewood, Goose Lake, Rauville, Gary,
Waverly, Kranzburg, Goodwin, Revillo, Brandt, Strandburg, Claremont
Colony, Troy, Altamont, Bemis, Bullhead Lake, Moritz, Lake Kampeska,
and Watertown City Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
